    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Dian<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan><surplus>e</surplus> et A<supplied reason="lost">pollini</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/>Capito IIvir co<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>oniae</ex></expan> et <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>na pro salute e<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="4"/>filiorum s<supplied reason="lost">uorum <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olverunt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibentes</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan></supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Basis einer Statuettengruppe (in 1 Stück gearbeitet); noch unterer Teil der Diana und eines Greifen(?) erhalten. Z. 4: unsicher, ob filior(u)m oder RVM-Ligatur. Datierung: Romula wurde wahrscheinlich unter Septimius Severus zur colonia erhoben. (B): CIL III 1588; Tudor: Leseabweichungen.</p>
            </div>
